title: The Tripartite Free Trade Area: Dr. Peter Karungu
description:
On June, COMESA, SADC and the East Africa Community launched the Tripartite Free Trade Area that stretches from Cape to Cairo. TFTA comprises 26 countries representing almost 57% or a trillion dollars of the Africa's GDP. However, the Africa Union is championing the Continental Free Trade Area (CFTA).

For more News visit: http://www.sabc.co.za/news
